tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting significant renal impairment and possible diabetic or metabolic derangement, despite a low HbA1c. Urine is dilute, cloudy, brown, and ammoniacal, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Further evaluation of renal function, diabetes status, and possible acute or chronic kidney disease is recommended.
